channel.title: [WiP]First real attempt to primitives. Re-doing my first model ever
channel.description:
Here is the wireframe to my first model ever Auron's Mastermune from FFX [IMG]http://i247.photobucket.com/albums/gg159/Ituharu_Yamada/WireFrameAuronSideView.png[/img]
Primitive Wireframe [IMG]http://i51.tinypic.com/ww0ytz.png[/img]
End of the night for today. [IMG]http://i52.tinypic.com/qrlpqx.png[/img]
Note: Just FYI, I'm horrible at keeping wireframes clean. This model currently stands at 318 faces.
I also need help removing unnecessary points on my wireframe when I use my knife. If anyone can point me in the right direction, I'd be glad. This will help me speed up the process of cleaning up my wireframe.
Will be working on it slowly due to Track & Field and school.

item.dc:creator: @drubrkletern drubrkletern
item.description:
@drubrkletern wrote:

[quote=“Ryan4965, post:11, topic:387454”][quote author=h1 sk1ller link=topic=483258.msg3539930#msg3539930 date=1300793047]
It’s probably traced but it might be triangulated, I bet it’s traced though.

If(Trace = false){
Awesome!
}
If(Trace = true){
Learn prims
}

ignore my coding I know it fails…
[/quote]

Correction:

If(Trace == false){
Awesome!
}
If(Trace == true){
Learn prims
}

A singular equals sign makes the compiler think that you’re trying to change the value, whereas the double equals sign shows that your getting the value, rather than changing it.
Just a tip ^^[/quote]

If(Trace == true) { sendMessage("Gtfo faggot"); } else If(Trace == false) { sendMessage("Gj"); }
